title: working!!
body:
[b]WORKING!![/b] is a [[4koma]] by [[Takatsu Karino]], serialized in [b]Young Gangan[/b] since 2005. Originated from a [[working!! (web manga)|web manga]] started in 2002 also by Takatsu Karino.

The series has a TV anime adaptation which has run 3 seasons. The first season aired Spring 2010 and shared the same name as the manga. A second season aired Fall 2011 and was titled [i]Working'!![/i], with an apostrophe in the name.  The third and final season airing July, Summer 2015 and is titled [i]Working!!![/i], with three exclamation marks in the name. The alternative "export" name of the series is [b]Wagnaria!![/b] which is the name of the restaurant chain of the restaurant where most of the series takes place. 

It is a work-life comedy series with a quirky cast mostly consisting out of teens and young adults. Multiple characters in the series have feelings toward each other. However, this anime is for the most part not romance driven, so your mileage might vary.

title: gn_flag
body:
[b]SVMS-01X Union Flag Custom II "GN Flag"[/b]
A further modification of [[Graham Aker]]'s custom [[Union Flag]] equipped with the GN Drive Tau that was supposed to be installed in the GN-X unit intended for his personal use before he rejected it, citing personal reasons. The GN Drive was then installed on the Flag's left shoulder, with a connector cable powering the GN Beam Saber that had been taken from the [[Gundam Throne Eins]]. While it was a remarkably powerful unit, it still added up no more than a hasty modification of a machine that was not intended for GN Drive operation, so it lacked adequate G-force damping and put such considerable strain on Graham's body that he suffered grave internal injuries just from the maneuvering needed to keep up with the [[Gundam Exia]].

title: over_flag
body:
[b]SVMS-01O Over Flag[/b]
A further modification of the [[Union Flag]] intended for use by [[Graham Aker]]'s elite squadron, the "Overflags". Developed with piloting data from Graham's custom Flag, it boasts extreme performance at the cost of ease of handling - as it was intended to be used exclusively by ace pilots handpicked by Graham himself - and included innovations from the Custom Flag which made the unit greatly resemble a right-handed variant of Graham's personal, left-handed machine.

title: union_flag
body:
[b]SVMS-01 Union Flag[/b]
The Union's next generation general purpose MS, replacing the outdated Union Realdo. It built upon the Realdo's foundation, armed with the standard linear rifle and sonic blade, as well as carrying the defense rod for increased survivability. While it could also transform to and from a flight mode on the fly, this capacity was initially not used as a combat tool until demonstrated by [[Graham Aker]]'s extraordinary piloting skills, which led to this act of transforming in the midst of combat being dubbed the Graham Maneuver.

title: peter_b_parker
body:
[i]Janky, old, broke, hobo Spider-Man.[/i]

An older, alternate version of [[Peter Parker]] who appears in [[Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse]]. In his universe, he has been [[Spider-Man]] for 22 years, saved the city several times, and married [[Mary Jane Watson]]. Years of superheroics resulted in his marriage becoming testy, losing a lot of money on bad investments (including a Spidey-themed restaurant), burying his Aunt May, and eventually divorcing Mary Jane because he was afraid to have children. Despite his schlubby appearance, he's still more than capable of doing whatever a spider can.

title: elevator
body:
A type of vertical transport equipment that efficiently moves people or goods between floors (levels, decks) of a building, vessel or other structures. Elevators are generally powered by electric motors that either drive traction cables or counterweight systems like a hoist, or pump hydraulic fluid to raise a cylindrical piston like a jack.

h4. See also

* [[Escalator]]
* [[Scissor lift]]

title: scissor_lift
body:
A scissor lift is a mechanical lifting platform used to provide temporary access for people and equipment to elevated and inaccessible areas. The device achieves vertical movement through the use of linked folding supports arranged in a crisscross or scissors-like pattern. Scissor lifts are designed to lift limited weights (usually less than a ton) and are capable of being set up and operated by one person. They are sometimes used while performing surface preparation, coating, or inspection activities.

h4. See also

* [[Elevator]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia - Aerial work platform":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aerial_work_platform]

title: tor_browser
body:
A free and open source browser that makes all of its users anonymous. It is also one of the few browsers that can access .onion (deep and/or dark web) websites. People mostly use it for anonymity and some for illegal activities. Tor's logo is a [[red onion]], representing the layers of encryption it uses to anonymize its users.

title: pan_(dragon_ball)
body:
[[Dragon Ball]] character. First appearance being as a child at the end of the original manga series, while she had a major role in [[Dragon Ball GT]]. Pan is the only daughter of [[Son Gohan]] and [[Videl]], [[Son Goten]]'s niece, and [[Son Goku]], [[Chi-Chi (dragon ball)|]], and [[Mr. Satan]]'s granddaughter. Her name is derived from the Japanese term for "bread" (the Son family), the Greek god Pan (Mr. Satan and Videl) and the pan flute ([[Piccolo]]), creating a multilayered name befitting Toriyama's style.

h4. See also
* [[Pan (Xeno) (dragon ball)|]]

body:

title: imageboard_desourced
body:
From February of 2008 up to Late November of 2016, Danbooru rewrote select imageboard sources to "Image board" on upload, such as those from 4chan, Cynthia and Yande.re. Due to the nature of things, it is unlikely for those automatic changes to be reversed. (forum #122820)

As a result, post with such sources have automatically received the [[non-web source]] tag, due to their now-textual nature.

This tag is for such posts (as well as those posts that were manually desourced from their original by users uploading). If possible, the sources should be standardized for ease of access (forum #152518), if not restored if in any way possible. Posts which have had their sources changed to either their original first-party source, a different text source, or to nothing cannot reasonably be accounted for.

If the source is changed to the image's original first-party source, assuming the source in question is still active, and the md5/EXIF data might not match, please use topic #16765 to get the post replaced. For first-party sources that aren't available anymore ([[bad id]]), check tools such as SauceNAO and ascii2d, as to see if a link to them can still be obtained (though in such a case, this tag could arguably be retained on the post in question, due to how imageboards can potentially change that data; or if not, substituted with [[MD5 mismatch]] where appropriate).

title: isokaze_kai_(kancolle)
body:
Isokaze's Kai and Kai B forms, main differences between this and her base from are listed as following:  
In her remodel, her scarf has been changed to a rope, her thighhigh gains a stripe, the Standard 12.7cm guns have been replaced by their High-Angle equivalent, a radar has been propped behind her head and finally, camo-textures are added to her uniform.

For her B remodel (which is not an actual second remodel), she is essentially the same as in her remodel except for her use of long 10cm guns. While she is now significantly more powerful stats-wise, the portrait serves as an art refresher.
